pub fn jjrz_parse(vocabulary: &[jjrz_Slug], markdown: &str) -> Result<jjrz_Gazette, Vec<String>> {
    // ...
    for (line_idx, line) in markdown.lines().enumerate() {  // <-- SPLIT
        // ...
        if !in_fence && zjjrz_is_notice_boundary(line) {
            if let Some((slug, lede, content_lines, hdr_line)) = current.take() {
                zjjrz_finalize_notice(slug, &lede, &content_lines, hdr_line, &mut notices, &mut diagnostics);
            }
            // ... parse header ...
        } else if let Some((_, _, ref mut content_lines, _)) = current {
            content_lines.push(line.to_string());  // <-- Accumulate lines
        }
    }
}
```

**Finalize (join) path** (lines 344-374):
```rust
fn zjjrz_finalize_notice(slug, lede, content_lines, ...) {
    let content = zjjrz_trim_blank_lines(content_lines);
    // ...
    inner.insert(lede.to_string(), content);
}

pub(crate) fn zjjrz_trim_blank_lines(lines: &[String]) -> String {
    let start = lines.iter().position(|l| !l.trim().is_empty()).unwrap_or(lines.len());
    let end = lines.iter().rposition(|l| !l.trim().is_empty()).map(|i| i + 1).unwrap_or(0);
    if start >= end {
        String::new()
    } else {
        lines[start..end].join("\n")  // <-- JOIN
    }
}
```

**Emit (split again) path** (lines 224-247):
```rust
pub fn jjrz_emit(&self) -> String {
    self.frozen.set(true);
    let mut output = String::new();
    let mut first = true;
    for (&slug, inner) in &self.notices {
        for (lede, content) in inner {
            if !first {
                output.push('\n');
            }
            first = false;
            if lede.is_empty() {
                output.push_str(&format!("# {}\n", slug));
            } else {
                output.push_str(&format!("# {} {}\n", slug, lede));
            }
            if !content.is_empty() {
                output.push('\n');
                output.push_str(content);  // <-- Content is already a flat string (joined earlier)
                output.push('\n');
            }
        }
    }
    output
}
```

**The "sandwich"**: Content flows as:
1. **Split** (parse): Markdown text → `lines().collect()` → `Vec<String>` (line-by-line)
2. **Join** (finalize): `Vec<String>` → `.join("\n")` → `String` (flat, stored in notice map)
3. **Split** (emit): `String` → reconstructed with headers, no additional split

Docket text is stored as a **flat `String`** inside the gazette's notice map (entry 6 of the Tack struct, line 76 of jjrt_types.rs). The "sandwich" is purely internal to the gazette's parse/emit round-trip; docket text itself remains a `String` at rest.

